AUTHOR: Makar
dna_template_description: The DNA template was generated from an oligonucleotide encoding the first 11 codons of the ermBL gene from GenBank accession number AAA27451.2. The oligonucleotide was synthesized using 82 % of the wild-type nucleotide and 6% of each of the remaining 3 nucleotides in the coding region for ermBL in order to generate a deep-mutated version of the gene.
ligand_used_during_selectio: This is the reverse transcribed mRNA used as template in all ErmBL samples

AUTHOR: Makar
dna_template_description: The DNA templates encode the wild-type sequences of the known arrest peptides ermAL1(1-14) (GenBank accession number CAA26966.1), ermBL (1-17, according to Arenz et al. 2014, Nat Comm) (GenBank accession number AAA27451.2), ermCL(1-10) (gene bank accession number CAA24592.1), ermDL (sequence according to Sothiselvam et al. 2014, PNAS) (GenBank accession number AAA22598.1), secM(150-166) (GenBank accession number AAC73208.2) , and tnaC(12-24) (modified with an TAA stop codon, GenBank accession number AAC76730.1). The DNA templates were generated from oligonucleotides.
ligand_used_during_selectio: selection using inverse toeprinting in the presence of erythromycin (ermAL1, ermBL, ermCL, ermDL), tryptophan (tnaC-TAA) or without additional ligand (secM)
